ZH: 我们这次聚会真的破费了。
EN: We really splurged on this gathering.

ZH: 别破费了，我来付账。
EN: Don't worry about the expenses, I'll handle it.

ZH: 穿名牌衣服太破费了。
EN: It's too extravagant to wear branded clothes.

ZH: 这个婚礼一定会破费很多钱。
EN: This wedding will surely cost a lot of money.

ZH: 跟朋友出去玩总是破费不少。
EN: Going out with friends always incurs a lot of expenses.

ZH: 如果你选这个酒店，破费一定会很多。
EN: If you choose this hotel, the expenses will definitely be high.

ZH: 他喜欢破费买各种奢侈品。
EN: He likes to spend money on various luxury goods.

ZH: 我们经常因为奢侈品破费超过预算。
EN: We often exceed the budget due to the expenses on luxury goods.

ZH: 我没想到购物会破费到这个程度。
EN: I didn't expect shopping to be so expensive.

ZH: 在这个城市，吃饭破费相对便宜。
EN: Eating out is relatively cheap in this city.

ZH: 他不愿意破费去买一个新手机。
EN: He is unwilling to spend money on buying a new cellphone.

ZH: 这个旅行破费了我好几个月的工资。
EN: This trip cost me several months' salary.

ZH: 搬家肯定会破费一笔。
EN: Moving will definitely incur a considerable expense.

ZH: 买新家具需要破费很多钱。
EN: Buying new furniture requires a lot of money.

ZH: 这个电子产品的价格不算破费。
EN: The price of this electronic product is not considered extravagant.

ZH: 别再破费买奢侈品了，我们要节约。
EN: Don't spend money on luxury goods anymore, we need to save.

ZH: 破费去激光祛痘，效果不错。
EN: Spending money on laser acne treatment is effective.

ZH: 电影院的票价相对破费。
EN: Cinema ticket prices are relatively expensive.

ZH: 这个品牌的产品太破费了，质量也不好。
EN: This brand's products are too expensive and of poor quality.

ZH: 为了旅行不破费，我们选择住便宜的酒店。
